<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She recently returned to filming Countdown.  </p>

<p>And Rachel Riley cut a stylish figure once again as she left the studios in Manchester on Tuesday. </p>

<p>The co-host, 34, caught the eye in a black floral jumpsuit which she teamed with a neon pink cardigan. </p>

<p>Turning heads: Rachel Riley cut a stylish figure once again as she left the studios in Manchester on Tuesday after filming Countdown</p>

<p>Rachel showed off her long legs in the jumpsuit which were partially cropped on the leg. </p>

<p>She added a boost to her height with purple peep toe heels and accessorised her outfit with a patterned tote bag. </p>

<p>The television personality wore her blonde locks in a sleek straight do and accentuated her natural beauty with a polished make-up look.  </p>

<p>Gorgeous: The co-host, 34, caught the eye in a black floral jumpsuit which she teamed with a neon pink cardigan</p>

<p>Strutting her stuff: Rachel showed off her long legs in the jumpsuit which were partially cropped on the leg</p>

<p>She's got style: Rachel added a boost to her height with purple peep toe heels and accessorised her outfit with a patterned tote bag</p>

<p>Gorgeous: The television personality wore her blonde locks in a sleek straight do and accentuated her natural beauty with a polished make-up look</p>

<p>The outing comes as Rachel revealed her hopes for baby daughter Maven, nine months, to be bilingual as husband Pasha Kovalev only talks to her 'solely in Russian'.</p>

<p>The Countdown star appeared Good Morning Britain recently where she sweetly spoke about her family.</p>

<p>Discussing baby daughter Maven, she said: 'She's got teeth, she's biting us, she's all about chat chat chat!  </p>

<p>'Pasha is speaking to her solely in Russian and I'm speaking to her in English so we're hoping she'll be bilingual.'</p>

<p>Back to work: Filming has returned for Countdown, after it was halted during the coronavirus pandemic</p>

<p>High spirits: Rachel flashed a smile as she left the studios</p>

<p>Rachel sweetly added: 'She's so mobile, she's crawling and can walk with one hand now.'  </p>

<p>The maths whizz also shared that she will be teaching her daughter mathematics but joked: 'At the moment, she can bash cups together!'</p>

<p>Rachel also shared details of the regulations on set for Countdown amid the coronavirus pandemic. </p>

<p>Doting mum: The outing comes as Rachel revealed her hopes for baby daughter Maven, nine months, to be bilingual as husband Pasha Kovalev only talks to her 'solely in Russian'</p>

<p>She said: 'We were quite lucky, but we lost our audience which is a shame as they come time and time again, we're like a little family.</p>

<p>'The person who comes and takes the letters from me is in full hazmat gear and has a spatula!' </p>

<p>Rachel, Pasha and Maven have spent lockdown with her Russian mother-in-law Galina, whose month-long visit to the UK was extended amid the pandemic.   </p>

<p>The couple, who became first-time parents to Maven in December and met on Strictly Come Dancing, have enjoyed extended time off at home amid the global COVID-19 pandemic. </p>

